{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "roadresq-api-collection-v1",
    "name": "RoadResQ API",
    "description": "Complete REST API collection for the RoadResQ backend.\n\n**Base URL:** `http://localhost:3000`\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Import `RoadResQ_Local.postman_environment.json` as your environment\n3. Select the **RoadResQ Local** environment from the top-right dropdown\n4. Start the backend server: `cd backend && npm install && node server.js`\n5. Hit any endpoint!\n\n## Auth Flow\n- Call `POST /api/auth/register` to create a user\n- The `userId` will be auto-saved to your environment\n- Use the `userId` in job/driver calls",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🔐 Auth",
      "description": "Authentication endpoints — register and login users.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.status === 'success' && res.data && res.data.uid) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('userId', res.data.uid);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('userRole', res.data.role);",
                  "    console.log('✅ userId saved:', res.data.uid);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Response has success status', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(res.status).to.equal('success');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Kent Reyes\",\n  \"email\": \"kent@roadresq.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\n  \"phone\": \"+63 912 345 6789\",\n  \"role\": \"customer\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "**POST /api/auth/register**\n\nCreates a new Firebase Auth account + Firestore user document.\n\n**Roles:** `customer` | `driver` | `garage` | `admin`\n\n**Auto-saves `userId` to environment on success.**\n\n**Validation:**\n- `name` — required\n- `email` — required, valid email\n- `password` — required, min 6 chars\n- `phone` — required\n\n**Success Response (201):**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"uid\": \"abc123\",\n    \"name\": \"Kent Reyes\",\n    \"email\": \"kent@roadresq.com\",\n    \"phone\": \"+63 912 345 6789\",\n    \"role\": \"customer\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n  }\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Register Driver",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.status === 'success' && res.data && res.data.uid) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('driverUserId', res.data.uid);",
                  "    console.log('✅ driverUserId saved:', res.data.uid);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Juan Driver\",\n  \"email\": \"driver@roadresq.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\n  \"phone\": \"+63 917 000 0001\",\n  \"role\": \"driver\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Registers a driver account. After registering, create a driver profile using **POST /api/drivers**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Verify ID Token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.status === 'success') {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('userId', res.data.uid);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('userRole', res.data.role);",
                  "    console.log('✅ Logged in as:', res.data.name);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"idToken\": \"{{firebaseIdToken}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "**POST /api/auth/login**\n\nVerifies a Firebase ID Token (obtained from the Flutter client after sign-in) and returns the user profile from Firestore.\n\n**How to get the `idToken` from Flutter:**\n```dart\nfinal token = await FirebaseAuth.instance.currentUser?.getIdToken();\n```\n\n**Or for testing:** Get it from the Firebase Auth Emulator / REST API:\n```\nPOST https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com/v1/accounts:signInWithPassword?key=YOUR_API_KEY\nBody: { \"email\": \"...\", \"password\": \"...\", \"returnSecureToken\": true }\n```\nCopy the `idToken` from the response."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [""]
            },
            "description": "Server health check. Returns API version and all available endpoints."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
